>> title: Simple Stovetop Macaroni and Cheese
>> source: https://www.pbs.org/food/recipes/simple-stovetop-macaroni-cheese

Bring @water{1.5%cups} and @milk{1%cup} to boil in medium saucepan over high heat. Stir in @elbow macaroni{8%oz} and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring frequently, until macaroni is soft (slightly past al dente), 6 to 8 minutes. Add @American @extra-sharp cheddar @Parmesan cheese{2%tbsp}{4%oz}{4%oz}, @Dijon mustard{0.5%tsp}, and cayenne and cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is completely melted, about 1 minute. Off heat, stir in cheddar until evenly distributed but not melted. Cover saucepan and let stand for 5 minutes.

Meanwhile, combine panko, oil, 1/8 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon @pinch cayenne @Salt and pepper{}{} in 8-inch nonstick skillet until panko is evenly moistened. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until evenly browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Off heat, sprinkle Parmesan over panko mixture and stir to combine. Transfer panko mixture to small bowl.

Stir @elbow macaroni{8%oz} until sauce is smooth (sauce may look loose but will thicken as it cools). Season with @Salt and @pinch cayenne pepper{}{} to taste. Transfer to warm serving dish and sprinkle panko mixture over top. Serve immediately.
